<br>
On a slightly less bitter note, yes, you're right (though misguided). Welfare laws are completely out of control, and immigration laws are completely out of control. <br>
<br>
This is why you want &quot;these people&quot; in your country. Because every shit job in the world like washing your dishes after you take your pretty white girlfriend to Chili's or whatever or scraping the grease out of the grease trap at McDonald's. You know - the jobs most of &quot;us people&quot; are too lazy or too proud to do. <br>
<br>
A family of Mexicans moved into the house next door to me recently. Its an old 3 story house that was like many houses in the area taken over by &quot;blockbusters&quot; (not the video store chain) and cut up into 3 diff apartments to make room for low income housing. This by the way, is what contributes to the urbanization and decline of neighborhoods, eventually making them &quot;ghettos&quot; which you love to hate so much. <br>
<br>
Anyway, I digress. I'll be honest. These Mexicans fulfill a LOT of racial stereotypes. They are always working on a different car in the yard every week. They drink in the middle of the day (usually only on weekends) and play loud mariachi music. There seems to be an endless stream of children living in the house. Ya know what though? The men that live in the house go to work every day, and they work hard as hell. Harder than I do, and for a lot less money. They take care of the house - they painted it, and they're putting a new porch on it. They made a deal with my landlord to get the entire lot paved together so they could save money.<br>
<br>
Based on my anecdotal evidence, clearly I can conclude that all Mexicans are hard working people who take care of their family and take pride in their homestead.<br>
<br>
Look the bottom line is this. Leech scum are everywhere in this country. And they're all different colors. Hey, I sucked up your tax dollars for a whole month this summer, sitting on my ass and collecting unemployment. But I'm white, so do I get a free pass? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=550521"><br>
